gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 122, Pistons 113
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks defeated the Pistons, 122-113. Giannis Antetokounmpo recorded 31 points, 17 rebounds, and 10 assists for the Bucks, with Khris Middleton adding 26 points and two rebounds in the victory. Marcus Sasser tallied 23 points and three assists for the Pistons in the losing effort. The Bucks improve to 30-13, while the Pistons fall to 4-39.
